{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RBUA3aG5euw4Zz3gg86c1Q","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have gathered all the information. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've thoroughly searched the cloche daemon configuration system. Here are the key findings:\n\n### 1. **Database Path Configuration**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (line 42)\n\n```go\ndbPath := envOrConfig(\"CLOCHE_DB\", globalCfg.Daemon.DB, \"cloche.db\")\n```\n\n- **Environment variable:** `CLOCHE_DB`\n- **Config file location:** `~/.config/cloche/config` (loaded by `config.LoadGlobal()`)\n- **Config key:** `[daemon]` section, `db` field\n- **Default:** `cloche.db` (relative path to current working directory)\n- **Source code:** `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` lines 76-98\n\n### 2. **Socket Path Configuration**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (line 43)\n\n```go\nlistenAddr := envOrConfig(\"CLOCHE_LISTEN\", globalCfg.Daemon.Listen, \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\")\n```\n\n**Client side (cloche):**\n```go\naddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_ADDR\")\nif addr == \"\" {\n    addr = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\n}\n```\n\n- **Daemon environment variable:** `CLOCHE_LISTEN`\n- **Client environment variable:** `CLOCHE_ADDR`\n- **Config file location:** `~/.config/cloche/config` (loaded by `config.LoadGlobal()`)\n- **Config key:** `[daemon]` section, `listen` field\n- **Default:** `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`\n- **Socket handling:** Daemon uses `net.Listen(\"unix\", sockPath)` with `os.Remove(sockPath)` to clean up stale sockets (line 197)\n- **Files:** \n  - Daemon: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` lines 42-43, 194-201\n  - Client: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` lines 120-124, 720-723; `/workspace/cmd/cloche/project.go` lines 28-31\n\n### 3. **Log File Path Configuration**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 91-103)\n\nLogs are stored in SQLite database tables `log_files` and `step_executions`:\n- No separate log file directory configuration exists\n- Log entries are persisted to the same database file specified by `CLOCHE_DB`\n- HTTP log streaming is provided via `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/` and `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/` adapters\n\n**Related environment:** `CLOCHE_HTTP`\n- For daemon HTTP server address (enables web dashboard with log access)\n- Default: Not set (disabled unless configured)\n- Config key: `[daemon]` section, `http` field\n\n### 4. **Config Directory / Global Config**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` (line 86)\n\n```go\npath := filepath.Join(home, \".config\", \"cloche\", \"config\")\n```\n\n- **Global config location:** `~/.config/cloche/config` (TOML format)\n- **Per-project config location:** `<projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml` (loaded by `config.Load(projectDir)`)\n- **Config sections:** `[daemon]`, `[evolution]`, `[orchestration]`, and top-level `active` flag\n\n### 5. **Related Environment Variables**\n\nFrom `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go` lines 508-512:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_ADDR          Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\nCLOCHE_HTTP          Daemon HTTP address (for health/tasks commands)\nCLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run ID for get/set commands (set automatically in steps)\nCLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory override for get/set commands\n```\n\nAdditional daemon-side variables (from `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`):\n```\nCLOCHE_DB            Database file path (default: cloche.db)\nCLOCHE_LISTEN        Daemon listen address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\nCLOCHE_RUNTIME       Container runtime (default: docker, can be local)\nCLOCHE_IMAGE         Default container image (default: cloche-agent:latest)\nCLOCHE_HTTP          HTTP server address for web dashboard\nCLOCHE_AGENT_PATH    Path to cloche-agent binary (for local runtime)\nCLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND   LLM command for evolution trigger\n```\n\n### 6. **Configuration Loading Order**\