{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014wBaaawng9PHM7Xs8zGe9D","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015pRPphvuFe81MrThhJ4TDH","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspace/internal/config/config.go","old_string":"// LoadGlobalFrom reads the global config from a specific path.\n// Useful for testing.\nfunc LoadGlobalFrom(path string) (*Config, error) {","new_string":"// StateDir returns the path to ~/.config/cloche/ and ensures it exists.\n// Falls back to a temp directory if the home directory cannot be determined.\nfunc StateDir() string {\n\thome, err := os.UserHomeDir()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn filepath.Join(os.TempDir(), \"cloche\")\n\t}\n\treturn filepath.Join(home, \".config\", \"cloche\")\n}\n\n// EnsureStateDir creates the state directory if it doesn't exist.\nfunc EnsureStateDir() (string, error) {\n\tdir := StateDir()\n\tif err := os.MkdirAll(dir, 0755); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t}\n\treturn dir, nil\n}\n\n// DefaultDBPath returns the default database path: ~/.config/cloche/cloche.db\nfunc DefaultDBPath() string {\n\treturn filepath.Join(StateDir(), \"cloche.db\")\n}\n\n// DefaultSocketAddr returns the default Unix socket address: unix://~/.config/cloche/cloche.sock\nfunc DefaultSocketAddr() string {\n\treturn \"unix://\" + filepath.Join(StateDir(), \"cloche.sock\")\n}\n\n// LoadGlobalFrom reads the global config from a specific path.\n// Useful for testing.\nfunc LoadGlobalFrom(path string) (*Config, error) {"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1035,"cache_read_input_tokens":27741,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1035},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5198584e-272c-43f1-8cb6-6e012c141597","uuid":"ba291279-f